This confirms the stale directory still exists on worker01.

The kubelet is trying to create:

/var/lib/kubelet/plugins/kubernetes.io/csi/openshift-storage.cephfs.csi.ceph.com/e72b449cc2471be2998890717403bda0fc0255076ef5a70fb407931b59ebf6ba/globalmount

but that path already exists from a broken previous mount attempt.

You can fix this manually without reboot if the kernel mount is not wedged.

Do exactly this on worker01.


---

1. Debug node

oc debug node/worker01.bscf2000.samsung.local

Then:

chroot /host


---

2. Check if mount is active

mount | grep e72b449cc2471be2998890717403bda0fc0255076ef5a70fb407931b59ebf6ba

and:

findmnt | grep e72b449cc2471be2998890717403bda0fc0255076ef5a70fb407931b59ebf6ba


---

3. If mounted → lazy unmount

umount -lf /var/lib/kubelet/plugins/kubernetes.io/csi/openshift-storage.cephfs.csi.ceph.com/e72b449cc2471be2998890717403bda0fc0255076ef5a70fb407931b59ebf6ba/globalmount


---

4. Remove stale directory

rm -rf /var/lib/kubelet/plugins/kubernetes.io/csi/openshift-storage.cephfs.csi.ceph.com/e72b449cc2471be2998890717403bda0fc0255076ef5a70fb407931b59ebf6ba


---

5. Restart kubelet

systemctl restart kubelet

Wait about 60-90 seconds.


---

6. Restart CephFS CSI plugin pod on worker01

Get pod:

oc get pod -n openshift-storage -o wide | grep cephfs

Delete the one on worker01:

oc delete pod <cephfsplugin-pod> -n openshift-storage


---

7. Recreate failed CNF pods

oc delete pod bscf2000-bip0-865dcc48dc-7z7g2 -n cnf

Then watch:

oc get po -w


